{
  "stem": "25598.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So back to 1940, '41, when things started getting worse and worse for the Jewish people in town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And when we had to wear the yellow star, and when there were curfews and you weren't allowed to do a myriad of things.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they didn't impact on me that much, because I was too small to, to be in the adult world, which was restricted.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, I do remember some incidents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One of them which had a significant impact on me was-- oh, we also had to close the, the windows, the glass.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anything that was glass in the house, windows or doors, had to be closed so that the light cannot be seen outside, because there were Soviet Russian planes and something.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was-- everything was camouflaged.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We weren't allowed to go out on the street late.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one day, there was an announcement that all the men had to gather in the building of the temple.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And they were holding-- the Iron Guard was holding the men hostage until-- I don't remember how-- what quantity of money and gold and silver is delivered to them from the community.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they threatened that if that will not be done, then they will burn the building with the men in the building.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was, of course-- that was the first big threat, the first big physical threat.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were psychological threats before, listening to the radio, listening to what's happening in other places, or anti-Semitic comments, or, or gestures, or swearing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But this was the first physical threat to the community, the fact that all the men were taken and locked up in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were not being given water.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were not being given food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT]",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
